definitions.definition: A road , street , or similar thoroughfare .
A narrow passageway between fences , walls , hedges or trees .
examples: There's a shortcut to the shops through this leafy lane .

definitions.definition: A narrow road, as in the country .
A lengthwise division of roadway intended for a single line of vehicles .
examples: Drivers should overtake in the outside lane
We were held up by a truck in the middle lane of the freeway.

definitions.definition: A similar division of a racetrack to keep runners apart.
examples: There are eight lanes on an Olympic running track.

definitions.definition: A similar division of a swimming pool using lines of coloured floats to keep swimmers apart.
Any of a number of parallel tracks or passages.
examples: the checkout lanes in a supermarket

definitions.definition: A course designated for ships or aircraft .
An elongated wooden strip of floor along which a bowling ball is rolled.
examples: We booked a couple of lanes at the bowling alley.

definitions.definition: An empty space in the tableau , formed by the removal of an entire row of cards.
Any of the parallel slots in which values can be stored in a SIMD architecture .
In MOBA ( multiplayer online battle arena ) games, a particular path on the map that may be traversed by enemy characters.

examples: And it's Uncle Mo in front by two as they come to the top of the lane .
